, anything-goes sense of fun. Wonderfully imaginative… smile-inducing… impressive.\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Stephen Brookes, The Washington Post (Washington, DC)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"The mastery of the performance was exquisite… together, they became a single body of energy.  The impact was huge.\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Makiko Ishihara, Bits Lounge Magazine (Toronto, ON)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"The artistic quality of their music is so far above anything we have had on stage.  Folks, young and old, [were] dancing… they had the audience in the palm of their hands!\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Julia Phillips, Artistic Director, Blue Skies Music Festival (Clarendon, ON)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"An absolutely riveting experience… pure and radiant talent!  The audience response... has been tremendous!\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Hillary McAndrew-Plate, Senior Manager, Lincoln Center (New York, NY)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"They are a force of epic proportion... it is almost impossible to believe that there are only three musicians on stage.  <em>Sonic Escape</em> is in the process of becoming an American Treasure.\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Terry Marshall, Senior Coordinator, Touhill Performing Arts Center (St. Louis, MO)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"…I could fill the review page with the word, PERFECT, in a very large type!\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-David Nichols, Selection Committee Chair, Sarnia Concert Association (Sarnia, ON)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"...opening listeners\' minds to sounds and ideas they\'d never previously considered...\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Aidan Connolly, Executive Director, Irish Arts Center (New York, NY)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"... the band left the stage to thunderous applause.\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Geoff Shields, The Sioux Lookout Bulletin (Sioux Lookout, ON)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"It is rare for our audience members to immediately ask us to re-engage artists... <em>Sonic Escape</em> was one of those rarities. \"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-John Ashton, President, Fairmont Chamber Music Society (Morgantown, WV)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"I\'ve been to performances all over Europe and America, and I can think of none I\'ve enjoyed more.\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Bradley Russell, Audience Member (Erie, PA)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"After many of your songs, I couldn\'t help but chuckle.  There was such life and joy.  The joy welled up and burst out!\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Dave Rockwood, Audience Member (Fairmont, WV)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"That was one of the best musical experiences of my life!  Can I give you a hug?\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Guy Jackson, Audience Member (Gravenhurst, ON)</b></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n\"Delightful young and enthusiastic kids.  They played from their lives, and bounced around the stage and hall.  All nations, all Bach/Irish, all compositions were excellently played.  Folk, Classical.  Wow!\"\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Review by Ratevka on Goldstar (Berkeley, CA)</b></span>','Quotes','','publish','closed','open','','quotes','','','2014-04-29 02:13:04','2014-04-29 02:13:04','',43,'http://dev.sonicescapemusic.com/?page_id=73',0,'page','',0),(74,1,'2014-01-19 23:45:29','2014-01-19 23:45:29','','Quotes/Comments','','inherit','closed','open','','73-revision-v1','','','2014-01-19 23:45:29','2014-01-19 23:45:29','',73,'http://dev.sonicescapemusic.com/73-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(81,1,'2014-01-20 00:30:59','2014-01-20 00:30:59','News fud goes here','News','','inherit','closed','open','','63-revision-v1','','','2014-01-20 00:30:59','2014-01-20 00:30:59','',63,'http://dev.sonicescapemusic.com/63-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(80,1,'2014-01-20 00:17:49','2014-01-20 00:17:49','About text goes here','','','inherit'