led and how it came to be.  <a href=\"http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Ancient-Dances.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Click for more info</span></a>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #8a359c;\">Japan Meets World</span></h3>\r\nAn exploration of Japan\'s most beloved folk songs and anime soundtracks.  Also featured are contemporary chamber works and Maria\'s compositions (for flute, violin, cello, voice &amp; dance) that transform western instruments into a traditional Japanese orchestra.  <a href=\"http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Japan-Meets-World.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Click for more info</span></a>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #8a359c;\">Echoing Voices: A Musical History of America - <i>Educational Outreach</i></span></h3>\r\nMusic from the homelands of immigrants through their stories and history of coming to America.  The music of 10 regions - the Netherlands, England, Ireland, Germany, Russia, Italy, Puerto Rico, Mexico, Egypt and China - is featured alongside interactive activities for audience members of all ages.  (Canadian version of <i>Echoing Voices</i> also available.)  <a href=\"http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Echoing-Voices.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Click for more info</span></a>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #8a359c;\">Classical and Folk</span></h3>\r\nAn investigation of the ties between folk and classical music from the European and American traditions, including dance rhythms, audience requests, lively sing-alongs, a Q&amp;A session and historical commentary.  Flute &amp; violin program.  <a href=\"http://youtu.be/Bcw3BYut0qQ\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Click for video</span></a>','More','','inherit','closed','open','','104-revision-v1','','','2014-02-08 12:39:40','2014-02-08 12:39:40','',104,'http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/104-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(289,1,'2014-01-27 05:51:42','2014-01-27 05:51:42','<span style=\"color: #000000;\">\"The artistic quality of their music is so far above anything we have had on stage. Folks, young and old, [were] dancing… they had the audience in the palm of their hands!\"</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b><i>- Julia Phillips, Artistic Director, Blue Skies Music Festival (Clarendon, ON)</i></b><span style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n\r\n\"An absolutely riveting experience… pure and radiant talent! The audience response... has been tremendous!\"\r\n</span><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b><i>- Hillary McAndrew-Plate, Senior Manager, Lincoln Center (New York, NY)</i></b><span style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n\r\n\"They are a force of epic proportion... it is almost impossible to believe that there are only three musicians on stage. Sonic Escape is in the process of becoming an American Treasure.\"\r\n</span><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b><i>- Terry Marshall, Senior Coordinator, Touhill Performing Arts Center (St. Louis, MO)</i></b><span style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n\r\n\"...opening listeners\' minds to sounds and ideas they\'d never previously considered...\"\r\n</span><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b><i>- Aidan Connolly, Executive Director, Irish Arts Center (New York, NY)</i></b><span style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n\r\n\"The mastery of the performance was exquisite… together, they became a single body of energy. The impact was huge.\"\r\n</span><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b><i>- Makiko Ishihara, Bits Lounge Magazine (Toronto, ON)</i></b><span style=\"color: #000000;\">\r\n\r\n\"I\'ve been to performances all over Europe and America, and I can think of none I\'ve enjoyed more.\"\r\n</span><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b><i>- Bradley Russell, Audience Member (Erie, PA)</i></b>','Quotes/Comments','','inherit','closed','open','','73-revision-v1','','','2014-01-27 05:51:42','2014-01-27 05:51:42','',73,'http: